HEADWORD: Broomy
<hw>Broom"y</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to
broom; overgrowing with broom; resembling broom or a broom.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If land grow mossy or <qex>broomy</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Mortimer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Brose</ent>⟦br⟧
